---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config";
---

<BaseLayout title={SITE.name}>
  <h1>{SITE.name}</h1>

  <p class="contact-row">
    <a href={SITE.githubUrl}>{SITE.githubLabel}</a>
    <span class="sep">·</span>
    <span>{SITE.emailDisplay}</span>
  </p>

  <p>
    I'm an undergraduate at UC Berkeley with a broad interest in optimization,
    spanning theoretical algorithms to machine learning. In practice, this has
    ranged from building a competitive chess engine in C++ to working on
    efficient ML inference. I like approaching problems from first principles,
    and have recently been moving further into systems and hardware.
  </p>

  <p>
    I grew up in New York. I enjoy competitive programming, used to play chess
    competitively, and play piano. I also bake — not particularly well, but
    I've thoroughly optimized the process of making almost-perfect macarons.
  </p>

  <section>
    <h2>Currently</h2>
    <p>
      I'm interning at MatX as an ML researcher, working on sparse attention to
      shift LLM decode from the memory-bound regime toward compute — primarily by
      reducing which KV cache entries are loaded at each step. I'm also an
      undergraduate researcher at BAIR in the Pallas group, working on making
      video generation more efficient through VAE optimization and sparse methods
      for diffusion language models. At Berkeley, I'm involved in Machine Learning
      at Berkeley on the education and research committees; through ML@B, I wrote
      NKI kernels for AWS Trainium 2 as part of a contracted project with Amazon
      Annapurna Labs.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Selected work</h2>
    <dl class="worklist">
      <dt>Altair Chess Engine</dt>
      <dd>
        A formerly top-30, 3600+ rated chess engine in C++, downloaded over 3000
        times and competitive in the CCC and TCEC championships.
      </dd>

      <dt>Annapurna Labs (Contract)</dt>
      <dd>
        Fused NKI kernels for attention and 3D-RoPE on AWS Trainium 2, with
        roofline analysis and MFU optimization for video diffusion inference.
      </dd>
    </dl>
    <p class="more-link">
      <a href="/projects">All projects →</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
